<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">This sample demonstrates about PivotGrid's Field List that allows you to add or remove an item, to or from PivotGrid's Grouping Bar.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images/FieldList.PNG" Stretch="None" /></Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center" FontFamily="Cambria" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="14">Field List displayed over PivotGrid</Paragraph>

<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}">Features:</TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>

<List Margin="20,20,0,0">
<ListItem>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">You can add or remove items in Grouping Bar using dynamic Field List. Grouping Bar is populated with items specified in the PivotFields property of PivotGrid control that allows you to add items in Grid during run-time.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
</List>

